channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Fani Willis likely to defy Georgia state Senate subpoena ahead of hearing Friday, chairman says
item.description: District Attorney Fani Willis is expected to defy a Georgia state senate subpoena for her testimony ahead of a hearing Friday, Fox News has learned.

item.title: Alaska high court lets man serving a 20-year sentence remain in U.S. House race
item.description: The Alaska Supreme Court ruled Thursday that a man currently serving a 20-year prison sentence can remain on the November ballot in the state's U.S. House race.

item.title: The Real Scandal in Springfield, Ohio
item.description: The cats and dogs may be safe and sound, but all is not right in Springfield.

item.title: First Ballots Mailed Out Closer To The Biden-Harris Switcheroo Than Election Day
item.description: As ballots started to go out in the mail this week, Kamala Harris' presidential candidacy had yet to hit its halfway mark.

item.title: House GOP rolling out bill to block China from accessing US ports
item.description: FIRST ON FOX: GOP Rep. Michelle Steele is rolling out a bill to block China and other American adversaries from accessing U.S. ports.

item.title: Trump adds to economic plan with vow to end taxes on overtime wages
item.description: Former President Donald Trump pledged Thursday to end all taxes on their overtime pay, saying it is time for the "working man and woman to finally catch a break."

item.title: Trump’s Terrible Tariffs
item.description: Perhaps the strongest indictment of his trade policies is that Joe Biden looked at them and thought they were worth continuing.

item.title: New York Times: It’s OK To ‘Help’ Your Mentally Incapacitated Relatives Complete Their Ballots
item.description: The New York Times said even if it is unclear whether someone is mentally capable, 'err on the side of helping someone to vote.'

item.title: 'It'll upend the community': PA town roiled by talk of migrant housing in Civil War-era orphanage building
item.description: An organization linked to a Civil War-era orphanage property has sought to host about 1,000 unaccompanied migrant minors, according to local lawmakers and correspondence.

item.title: Harris, Trump both barnstorm battleground states and declare debate victory
item.description: Former President Donald Trump traveled to Arizona to declare that he notched a "monumental victory" over "comrade" Vice President Kamala Harris in their first -- and likely only -- presidential debate.

item.title: Obamacare Is Still Wrecking Our Health-Care System
item.description: Plan quality is deteriorating as few doctors accept coverage.

item.title: Kamala Harris’ Pandering Tax Plan Is No Poverty Panacea
item.description: Harris wants to expand certain tax credits because they are popular with low-income voters, but her plan will increase the burden on taxpayers and supersize the national debt.

item.title: 'Very scary territory': Libertarian Party president fears what Harris could do to American Dream
item.description: Angela McArdle, president of the National Libertarian Party, told Fox News Digital she was not surprised by the results of a survey that showed only 9% of American voters think the American Dream is more attainable today.

item.title: Trump plans to launch his sons' crypto business on Monday, 50 days before Election Day
item.description: Former President Donald Trump plans to deliver remarks next Monday about cryptocurrency and the launch of the company World Liberty Financial, a crypto platform controlled by the Republican nominee's sons Donald Jr. and Eric.

item.title: Congress Fed Up with Canada’s Discriminatory Digital Tax
item.description: The really big sword hanging over Canada’s head right now is in Congress.

item.title: Nevada Activists Blast Elections Chief For Trying To ‘Discourage And Impede’ Legitimate Voter Roll Challenges
item.description: The Citizen Outreach Foundation is questioning a memo from Nevada Secretary of State Cisco Aguilar telling local officials to reject certain voter roll challenges.

item.title: Gov. Newsom signs bill to resume harsh penalties for smash-and-grab robberies in California
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom signed a bill Thursday that brings back harsh penalties for those who commit smash-and-grab retail thefts and other robberies.

item.title: U.S. population now has highest share of immigrants in its history
item.description: "The Census Bureau released today the 2023 American Community Survey (ACS), revealing a foreign-born or immigrant population (both legal and illegal) of 47.83 million in July of 2023 -- an increase of 1.65 million compared to the 2022 ACS results," advises the Center for Immigration Studies in a report released Thursday. "The foreign-born population size, along with the year-over-year growth, marks the largest the survey has ever recorded. At 14.3% of the total U.S. population, the share sets a new record for the survey," the report said.

item.title: The Week: The Debate and Its Aftermath
item.description: Plus: Cats and dogs in Ohio.

item.title: Kirby’s Reply-All Rebuff Of Veterans Confirms The Biden Administration’s Disdain For Our Military
item.description: Biden, Harris, and Kirby, not Trump, are the ones who repeatedly show contempt for men and women who have risked their lives for the country.
